<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS RELEASE CORNERBACK SMITH
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Former Cowboys cornerback Kevin Smith is retired
no more.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys officially removed Smith from the reserve/retirement
list and released him Tuesday. The nine-year veteran left the
Cowboys during training camp because of recurring back problems and
was offered an assistant coaching position with the team.
</P>
<P>
   Smith, however, still wants to play football, his agent, Stephen
Zucker, said.
</P>
<P>
   ``He's feeling pretty good,'' Zucker said.''That's why we went
to Dallas and withdrew his retirement letter. They either had to
put him on the roster or release him. He says he feels fine. He
hasn't taken a physical yet. But he wants to give it a shot.''
</P>
<P>
   Zucker said he talked to a few teams yesterday about Smith's
availability, though he said no deal was imminent. Zucker declined
to disclose those teams.
</P>
<P>
   According to a source, the New York Giants are one of a couple
of teams to express interest in Smith.
</P>
<P>
   Smith's decision to resume his career brings into question who
made the initial decision for him to leave the team after the Aug.
5 preseason game in Tokyo.
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys said then that Smith left because of frustration
stemming from a congenital degenerative disk in his lower back and
was contemplating retirement. Smith, who missed five weeks of
training camp and the first three games of the 1999 season because
of the back injury, struggled with his health and play during the
first two weeks of camp this season.
</P>
<P>
   According to a source, Smith wanted to continue his football
career, but eventually decided to retire to help the Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   Zucker declined to comment on the matter.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys owner Jerry Jones was unavailable for comment.
\Nsubheds:Moore expected to sign The Cowboys are expected to sign
rookie free-agent defensive tackle Ron Moore to the practice squad
today. Moore would take the spot vacated by quarterback Clint
Stoerner, who was promoted to the active roster last week.
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
<TRAILER>
NYT-09-13-00 0115EDT &QL; 
</TRAILER>
