<P>
   CAMPAIGN-VOLUNTEERS (Undated) _ For all the frenzied
fund-raising by both Democrats and Republicans this year,
candidates for offices from the the White House to the local school
board know that one thing is even more important than money:
volunteers. And while these unpaid armies are made up mostly of
students and retired people, it is business professionals who
exhibit the qualities that political candidates value the most:
nuts-and-bolts organizational skills, management savvy and
Rolodexes crammed with contacts. To campaign managers, these
executives are gold because they can get things done.
</P>
