A1647 &Cx1f; ttc-z
r s BC-BKN-MULLIN-LAKERS-LAD     09-13 0327
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-BKN-MULLIN-LAKERS-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
SOURCE: MULLIN TO LAKERS LIKELY
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By HOWARD BECK  
 c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News  
<TEXT>
<P>
   EL SEGUNDO, Calif. _ Like a frustrated game-show contestant, the
Lakers are once again reaching for the consolation prize after
wistfully watching the grand prize slip away.
</P>
<P>
   They coveted the rebounding skills of Horace Grant, but a
proposed three-team trade that would have made Grant a Laker, while
sending Glen Rice to New York, fell apart, leaving the Lakers
grasping for the nearest available help.
</P>
<P>
   That would be Chris Mullin, waived Tuesday by the Indiana
Pacers. Mullin can't fill the Lakers' gaping vacancy at power
forward, but he can provide depth at small forward in anticipation
of Rice's departure.
</P>
<P>
   The 37-year-old former Dream Teamer asked for, and was granted,
his release from the Pacers and must now clear the 48-hour waiver
period. Mullin is owed $4.6 million next season, so no team is
likely to claim him off waivers.
</P>
<P>
   Once he becomes a free agent on Thursday, the Lakers figure to
sign him for the veteran's minimum of $1 million _ a scenario
called ``likely'' by an NBA source.
</P>
<P>
   Mullin, a 15-year veteran, would give the Lakers another shooter
_ he made 44 percent of his 3-point tries the last three seasons _
and provide backup to either Kobe Bryant or Rick Fox at small
forward.
</P>
<P>
   Meanwhile, the Lakers' search for a power forward continues and
they are discussing a potential trade for Lorenzen Wright of the
Atlanta Hawks, sources said.
</P>
<P>
   Grant, currently with Seattle, would have been a nice fit here,
but the three-team deal died when the Knicks _ who would have sent
Patrick Ewing to the Sonics _ pulled out.
</P>
<P>
   Although reports surfaced Tuesday that the trade had died, a
knowledgeable source said the deal was never close and actually had
been off the table ``for four or five days'' by the time the
details leaked out last weekend. &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
