<P>
   LATIN-GRAMMYS _ For the first time, the National Academy of
Recording Arts and Sciences present the Latin Grammy awards,
recognizing achievement in music in this booming genre. We cover
the awards show live, plus run a list of winners. (MLongino,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 35.
</P>
<P>
   TV-OLYMPICS _ Looking for something to watch other than the
Olympics? Try 13 episodes of Survivor. Or ABC comedies in blocks
picked by viewers and celebrities. Those are just some of the
alternatives offered by CBS and ABC as the Peacock Network rolls
out the Olympic rings. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution).
</P>
<P>
   TV-ELIAN _ ``The Elian Gonzalez Story'' airs on Fox Family
Channel Sunday, 11 weeks after he went back to Cuba. Think that's
fast? Not even close to a record, as we revisit, in chart form, how
fast TV-movies about Amy Fisher, Waco, O.J. Simpson and others made
it on the screen. (Kloer, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 15.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-NOTES _ Tim Green's transition from pigskins to plot lines
has been relatively smooth. The former Atlanta Falcon and Phi Beta
graduate of Syracuse now has a law career, a TV career as a sports
announcer on Fox, and a writing career as a best-selling author.
And, after focusing on football as a theme in his other novels,
there's not a single punt or pass in his latest, ``The Letter of
the Law'' . . . Henry Hart, whose biography of James Dickey has
drawn harsh criticism from some quarters, talks about his book on
the eve of his visit to Emory University. (O'Briant, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   BOOKS-FRAILTY _ Feature/review on new book titled ``The Frailty
Myth,'' (it says that says women could be just as strong as men if
they got the right practice and training). With comments from Jan
Todd (one-time strongest woman in the world) at the UNiversity of
Texas. (Smith, Austin American-Statesman). WITH PHOTO.
</P>
<P>
   VIDEO-ROCK _ With ``Almost Famous'' opening Friday, Eleanor
Ringel Gillespie looks at rock music movies, including ``Rock 'N'
Roll High School'' and ``The Doors.'' (Ringel, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 18.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-REDDIRTGIRL _ A review of ``Red Dirt Girl,'' a new album
of mostly originals by Emmylou Harris. (Drennen, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 5 WITH PHOTOS.
</P>
<P>
   AUDIO-MINIS _ Mini reviews of new albums. (Atlanta
Journal-Constitution). 12.
</P>
<P>
   WRESTLING-GRAPEVINE _ Our wrestling columnist keeps up with the
latest twists and turns of the soap opera of professional wrestling
_ in the ring and behind the scenes. Love is in the air all around
professional wrestling circles. World Wrestling Federation
commentator Jim Ross reports in his weekly ``Ross Report'' that
``Stone Cold'' Steve Austin will marry Debra McMichael and Jerry
``The King'' Lawler will marry long-time girlfriend and WWF valet
The Kat this month. (Allen, Cox News Service) MOVED TUESDAY.
</P>
