<P>
   HOUSEWORK-POLL _ Guys, you're busted. Throughout the South,
husbands are claiming to do more housework than wives claim their
husbands are doing. Men took more credit for cooking, laundry and
housework in general than women allowed, a new AJC poll of married
adults found. In the housework category, for instance, 40 percent
of men said they either do it themselves or are an equal partner in
the housework. Meanwhile, just 23 percent of women said men do it
all or equally. Paula Jhung, author of ``How to Avoid Housework,''
isn't surprised. ``I think housework is like sex in that people lie
about it a lot,'' she says. ``Everybody claims they're doing more''
than they are. (Miller, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 25. WITH
PHOTOS.
