   FOOD-LATE _ It's 5:30...do you know what's for dinner? If you're
stuck in rush hour and you haven't the foggiest idea, you've no
doubt got lots of company. But if you think your only alternative
is takeout or something dumped out of a can, think again. With the
help of five notable metro Atlanta chefs who took our 5:30
Challenge, we show you how to get a delicious made-from-scratch
dinner on the table in less than 30 minutes, with a recipe that
uses no more than 5 ingredients that requires only the simplest of
sides. With these streamlined recipes, you also spend less time in
the supermarket and washing dishes afterward. What more could you
ask for on nights you long for the comfort of a home-cooked meal
but can't bear anything mentally or physically taxing in the
kitchen? This will kick off a new weekly feature in the food
section called The Five:30 Challenge, in which we share some of our
own 5-ingredient, 30-minutes recipes and invite readers to take the
