Sydney's Olympic strategy with Atlanta '96. Unlike Atlanta's highly
centralized zone of activity downtown, Sydney's game plan involves
separating most of the athletic events. That essential difference,
designed to take advantage of the natural ebb and flow of this
harbor town, is paramount as Sydney takes center stage Friday,
hoping to avoid some of Atlanta's embarrassing mistakes. There are
similarities, as well, including transportation problems that need
to get fixed for these spread-out Games to work right.
(Unger/Brock, Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 30. WITH GRAPHIC AND
PHOTOS.
