   OLY-WALKER _ When you talk about the Olympics, you have to talk
about the pressure. Unless you're Neil Walker. ``It's going to be
really fun,'' Walker said. If there's any athlete who's just happy
to be in Australia, it's Walker, a lanky Austin resident of Austin,
Texas and University of Texas swimmer. Four years ago he gained a
small measure of fame by missing the Olympics by the smallest of
margins, one-hundredth of a second as he was touched out for sixth
place in the 100 meter freestyle at the U.S. swim trials. In that
event, six swimmers can go to the Olympics for the 4X100 meter
freestyle relay team. This time around Walker could be anchoring
that race Saturday as well as later having a shot at medals in
another relay and two individual events. And that's after having a
couple of off swims and maybe one bad choice at the U.S. trials.
(Maher, Austin American-Statesman). 23.
</P>
