<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Locate hard to find itemsBy Marylin Johnson
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Having trouble finding a particular item? We'll try to help you
locate it. But because of the volume of mail, we cannot track down
every request. Readers whose queries are answered in the column
will receive a blue-and-cream canvas Buyer's Edge tote bag. Write
us at Buyer's Edge Find It,The Atlanta Journal-Constitution, P.O.
Box 4689, Atlanta, GA 30302; e-mail us at buyersedge(at)ajc.com
(please include your name, the city you live in and daytime phone
number); or call 404-582-7642
</P>
<P>
   Q: There's a new bug spray for home use called Bioganic. It's
used to eliminate ants, roaches, etc. I am interested since no
chemicals are in this product.
</P>
<P>
   _ Maurice Horowitz, Atlanta
</P>
<P>
   A: Bugs won't drive you buggy anymore with Bioganic, from
EcoSmart. The line of products offers action against a broad range
of critters including ants, wasps, hornets, fleas, flies and dust
mites. A 14-ounce can of the Flying Insect Killer or the Wasp and
Hornet Killer is $3.79 at Publix. We found our cans at the Ansley
Mall store, 1544 Piedmont Ave. N.E. (404-898-1850). Home Depot
stores also carry the products, including Bioganic Crawling Insect
Killer (14-ounce can, $4.46) and the Bioganic Dust Insecticide (a
12-ounce can, $4.96). We found ours at 815 Sidney Marcus Blvd. N.E.
(404-231-1411).
</P>
<P>
   Bioganic's active ingredients are made from plant and tree oils
that are widely used to add flavor and aroma to candy, frosting,
baked goods, frozen dairy products and lipstick. The formula also
contains Eugenol, a steam distilled extract from cloves. You can
also order these products online at: www.bioganic.com.
</P>
<P>
   Q: Where can I find Pickapeppa Hot Red Pepper Sauce? When I was
in Jamaica, I fell in love with it. I can find their brown sauce
but not the hot red sauce.
</P>
<P>
   _ Bob Swigart,
</P>
<P>
   Covington
</P>
<P>
   A: Peter Piper might have picked a peck of peppers but we found
your Pickapeppa Hot Red Pepper Sauce. You can order it from the
importer, Warbac Sales of Metairie, La. (504-834-1395). Twenty-four
3-ounce bottles are about $45. Or order online at:
www.pickapeppa.com. You can buy just one bottle for $3.
</P>
<P>
   Since 1921, this hot red sauce has been exported from Jamaica.
Key ingredients include hot peppers, sugar cane vinegar, salt and
spices. When asked how hot this sauce is, importer Warren H.A.
Backer simply said ``very hot.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: My boss is looking for a meat seasoning called Pinchitos,
which he says gives meat a wonderful flavor. He first bought it
when stationed in Spain during the '70s. For some time, he's been
trying to find it in the Atlanta area, but without success. Can you
help?
</P>
<P>
   _ Babs Hansard, Snellville
</P>
<P>
   A: Your boss should give you a raise! We asked a friend, Pilar
Amir, when she was visiting in Seville, Spain, if she could find
the seasoning and bring it back to us. Pinchitos is quite popular
in Spain and used as a marinade when mixed with oil or wine for
meat shish kebabs. It costs about 63 cents for a small pouch
encased in a yellow box adorned with a Moor's face. Ingredients
include oregano, cumin, caraway, turmeric, cilantro, anise, cayenne
pepper, clove, nutmeg and garlic. Unfortunately, the company does
not export to the United States. If a trip to Spain is not in your
plans, fax an order to the Productos Ruca Company at 0 11 34
958-402875. Or, you can contact major department stores in Spain _
such as El Corte Ingles _ which also stock the product.
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for Penaten Cream. It's a baby cream made in
Germany. Not only is it good for babies but the cream is also great
on the skin of allergy-prone adults. Please help.
</P>
<P>
   _ Gayle Breneman,
</P>
<P>
   Avondale Estates, Ga
</P>
<P>
   A: It's time to baby that skin again. We spotted your cream at
King's Drugs, 2345 Peachtree Road N.E. (404-233-2101). A 2-ounce
blue tin is $8.89. According to the manufacturer, the cream ``is
intended for delicate skins and is recommended to prevent and
relieve skirn irritation due to diaper-rash, chafing, prickly heat
and sunburn.''
</P>
<P>
   Q: I am looking for old-fashioned shelf paper, in white or
cream, on a roll, about 12-15 inches wide. And I want it
non-adhesive. Thank you.
</P>
<P>
   _ Jayne Buckwalter,
</P>
<P>
   Stone Mountain, Ga.
</P>
<P>
   A: Extend your shelf life with Royal Lace's Big Bargain Paper.
This lining paper (13 inches by 48 feet or 18 feet by 35 feet) is
$2.29 a roll at Richard's Variety Store, 2347 Peachtree Road N.E.
(404-237-1412). In addition to lining shelves and drawers, the
paper can also be used as disposable table covers or for scribbling
and drawing paper by your kids.
</P>
<P>
   _Contributing: Michelle C. Brooks
