   &UR; INTERNATIONAL &LR;
</P>
<P>
   EUROPE-FUEL (London) _ Some gasoline starts flowing again as
Prime Minister Tony Blair, mindful of protests that have brought
down other prime ministers, grapples with the political crisis. By
Warren Hoge.
</P>
<P>
   MIDEAST-PALESTINIANS (Jerusalem) _ On the day that Palestinians
had set for declaring statehood, two factions of the party of
Yasser Arafat, the Palestinian leader, clashed violently in Gaza
over an internal issue. By Deborah Sontag.
</P>
<P>
   FRANCE-MCDONALDS (Paris) _ A farmer who attacked a McDonald's in
an anti-globalization protest has been sentenced to three months in
jail, a longer sentence than prosecutors had asked for. By Suzanne
Daley.
</P>
<P>
   INDONESIA-BOMB (Jakarta) _ A car bomb ripped through an
underground garage in the Jakarta Stock Exchange building
Wednesday, killing at least one person, wounding at least 23 people
and possibly trapping others in choking smoke. (No byline)
</P>
<P>
   U.N. (Undated Nations) _ General Assembly developments. By
Christopher S. Wren.
</P>
<P>
   CORRUPT-NATIONS (United Nations) _ Transparency International's
annual index of the most corrupt countries focused this year on how
hard it is for a country to reverse its image once it has been
perceived as deeply corrupt. The end of military rule and a free
election in Nigeria, for instance, does not change the world's
perception of that country. By Barbara Crossette.
</P>
<P>
   WORKER-UNIONS (Geneva) _ A survey by an international labor
union group has found that being a union organizer is a precarious
position to hold all around the world. By Elizabeth Olson.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; WASHINGTON &LR;  (``w'' code)
</P>
<P>
   VIOLENCE-KIDS (Washington) _ More hearings on media violence and
kids. By David E. Rosenbaum.
</P>
<P>
   CONGRESS-HATE-CRIMES (Washington) _ The Democrats have offered a
measure that would put the House on record for favoring hate crimes
legislation. President Clinton is scheduled to hold a White House
news conference to rally support for a step he calls one of his top
legislative priorities for the year. By Lizette Alvarez.
</P>
<P>
   &UR; POLITICS &LR;  (``p'' code)
