<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-TRIVIA-Q&AMP;A-TEX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
PASS THE SPAGHETTI, PLEASE
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 By ROGERS CADENHEAD 
 c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
<TEXT>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ Did the term ``spaghetti western'' come from the
decision to shoot the Clint Eastwood film ``For a Few Dollars
More'' in Italy? _ G.M., via the Internet A:.MDNM/ The inspiration
was ``Fistful of Dollars,'' the 1964 Italian movie that
``single-handedly invented the `spaghetti western,' '' according to
film critic Leonard Maltin.
</P>
<P>
   ``Fistful'' was the first of three films directed by Sergio
Leone that starred Clint Eastwood as the Man With No Name. It was
followed by ``For a Few Dollars More'' and ``Good, the Bad, and the
Ugly.''
</P>
<P>
   In the early '60s, to meet the high demand for American westerns
in Europe, Leone and other filmmakers recruited American actors to
appear in foreign productions.
</P>
<P>
   ``For many people, the term `spaghetti western' is simply a
throwaway phrase that is used to describe four or five films made
by Sergio Leone,'' Lee Broughton writes in ``DVD Savant.'' ``But
Leone's films, seemingly the only genre films to have retained any
kind of a public profile, actually inspired the production of over
600 other European westerns.''
</P>
<P>
   ``DVD Savant'' is published on the Web at
www.dvdresource.com/savant.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ I'm moving to Houston early next year. How can I
request ticket information on the new NFL franchise that is
starting up there? _ T.B., Haltom City, Texas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ Call the Houston Texans at (832) 200-2002 or visit the
Web site www.houstontexans.com.
</P>
<P>
   The team, which begins play in the 2002 NFL season, unveiled its
logo and nickname this month. Team owner Bob McNair also considered
the names Apollos and Stallions before choosing Texans.
</P>
<P>
   The Dallas Cowboys have agreed to an annual preseason game
against the Texans, a revival of the Governor's Cup game that took
place against the Houston Oilers before they relocated and became
the Tennessee Titans.
</P>
<P>
   An earlier Texans team played in Dallas from 1960 to 1962 in the
American Football Conference. The team moved to Kansas City as the
Chiefs.
</P>
<P>
   Q:.MDNM/ How many black players are there in the National Hockey
League? _ C.C., Dallas
</P>
<P>
   A:.MDNM/ During the 1999-2000 season, 19 black athletes were on
NHL rosters out of 650 players, according to Information Please.
</P>
<P>
   The list includes two Americans, Mike Grier and Donald Brashear,
and one Nigerian, Rumun Ndur. Others include Anson Carter, Jarome
Iginla, Peter Worrell, Fred Brathwaite, Sandy McCarthy, Kevin
Weekes and Jason Doig, all from Canada.
</P>
<P>
   The first black player in the NHL was Willie O'Ree, who skated
for the Boston Bruins from 1958 to 1961. The next was Mike Marson
in 1974.
</P>
<P>
   Grant Fuhr, who became the sixth in 1981, retired this month
with 403 career wins and five Stanley Cup victories as goaltender
for the Edmonton Oilers. &QL; 
 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   (Rogers Cadenhead writes a trivia column for the Fort Worth
Star-Telegram. He can be reached at the Star-Telegram, Box 1870,
Fort Worth, Texas 76101; or by E-mail at trivia(at)prefect.com.
Visit the Star-Telegram's online services on the World Wide Web:
www.star-telegram.com) &QL;   &QL; 
nn
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
