   BRITAIN-FUEL (London) _ It's a study in chaos as Britons
hoarding gasoline and food show little faith in Tony Blair's
promise to get the crisis under control. About 90 percent of
Britain's 13,000 service stations remained closed. By Kevin Cullen.
1000 words.
