 &HT;    CLINTON PLANS TRIP TO TEXAS
 &HT;    c.2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   WASHINGTON _ President Clinton plans a two-city Texas trip Sept.
27, combining some political fund-raising with an address to gay
Democrats, the White House announced Wednesday.
</P>
<P>
   Clinton is scheduled to travel first to Dallas, where he's
slated to address the Democratic National Committee's Gay and
Lesbian Leadership Council.
</P>
<P>
   From there, he continues aboard Air Force One to Houston to
speak at an evening fund-raising reception for Rep. Max Sandlin,
D-Texas.
</P>
<P>
   He returns to Washington ``very late in the evening,'' said
White House spokesman Joe Lockhart.
</P>
