<P>
   MOTOROLA _ Motorola Inc.'s chip business names a top sales
executive as the new head of its manufacturing and related
operations. Hans Wildenberg, 44, a native of the Netherlands, is
the new manufacturing honcho, following the promotion of his
predecessor, Bill Walker, to general manager of the semiconductor
business. Wildenberg's promotion signals Motorola's commitment to
implementing more e-business processes in dealing with customers
and to sharing more information with them. Janelle Harris, replaces
Wildeberg as head of global sales. (Ladendorf, Austin
American-Statesman)
