<P>
   FLYING-ONLINE _ATLANTA _ Small airlines are better than big ones
when it comes to generating Internet bookings. Take AirTran
Airways, which now gets about a quarter of its bookings online,
with the number jumping as high as 40 percent during sales. Online
bookings at big airlines are still around 8 to 10 percent but
steadily building. The payoff for airlines is drastically reduced
processing costs. A look at the trend and where it's going. (Fonti,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution)
