<P>
   FBN-FALCONS-O-LINE _ FLOWERY BRANCH, Ga. _ While most of the
attention has focused on the struggles of the Atlanta Falcons
defense, the offensive line has had its share of problems during
the first two weeks of the season. Bob Hallen, the team's starting
left guard, was so ineffective in Sunday's loss to Denver that he
was eventually replaced by Chris Banks, who has been with the team
only two weeks. Ephraim Salaam and rookie Travis Claridge have
split time at right tackle, neither player stepping up to solidify
their hold on the position. All of the inconsistency has limited
the effectiveness of running back Jamal Anderson and could possibly
jeopardize the health of quarterback Chris Chandler. (Winkeljohn,
Atlanta Journal-Constitution). 18.
