<P>
   COXNET TRAVEL 0916: RETURN TO MAYBERRY -- Mount Airy, N.C., has
become a quiet mecca for cultists of black-and-white TV reruns and
archaeologists of 1960s innocence. Each year, thousands make the
pilgrimage to this tidy town in the Blue Ridge Mountains to
preserve the memory of the town's most celebrated citizen: Andy
Griffith. You see, Mount Airy is renowned for its alter-ego _ that
as Mayberry, the mythical setting for ``The Andy Griffith Show.''
(Moffett, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a 3-column color photo of
downtown Mount Airy, a 2-column color photo of a barbershop and a
18-pica color photo of an old-fashioned police car.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Trivia questions from ``The Andy Griffith Show.''
</P>
<P>
   WITH: FLORIDIAN IN DULUTH: Minnesotans don't realize that most
of us in Florida think they're crazy for living there. So I risk
severe condemnation for releasing the following secret: Duluth is a
beautiful city, among the best places in the United States to spend
the early fall. (Bierman, Palm Beach Post) Art includes a 18-pica
color photo of a waterfalls near Duluth, Minn.
</P>
<P>
   WITH: Travel briefs, including A Faberge exhibit in Delaware.
(New York Times News Service)
