<P>
   TRAVEL-SCOTS _ A heritage journey though southwestern North
Carolina makes a Celtic connection. We take you to Scottish Woods
Resort in Murphy, the Scottish Tartans Museum in Franklin, a neat
gift shop called Celtic Crown in Highlands and exhibit on
``Migration of the Scotch-Irish People'' at the Mountains Heritage
Center at Western North Carolina Univeristy. (Pousner, Atlanta
Journal-Constitution) WITH PHOTOS
</P>
<P>
   TRUCK-LOVE _ Loving a truck is different than loving a car, and
people love trucks. Loving a truck is buying that old heap off your
friend Dave for $700, manual choke, wrath-of-God noisy, about seven
miles to the gallon and mercy, is it ugly _ banged and scratched
and five different colors, including rust. But it's tough like a
bulldog and strong as a team of Clydesdales. Sauer, Grand Junction,
Colo.)
</P>
