<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-COWBOYS-AIKMAN0914-COX </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>
&HT;   
</HEADLINE>
 &HT;    Aikman appears ready to play Monday against Redskins
 &HT;    By Rick Cantu
 &HT;    c. 2000 Cox News Service
<TEXT>
<P>
   Cowboys Quarterback Troy Aikman returned to practice Wednesday,
a sign that he will play in Monday night's game in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   Aikman traded snaps with Randall Cunningham, who played well
Sunday in Arizona. Aikman did not complain about the headaches he
had after suffering a concussion 11 days ago against Philadelphia.
</P>
<P>
   Coach Dave Campo said Aikman's status for the next game might be
made today. If Wednesday is any indication, there is little doubt
Aikman will play if he continues to feel good throughout the
weekend.
</P>
<P>
   ``He looks exactly the same to me,'' wide receiver Wane McGarity
said. ``He looks fine.''
</P>
<P>
   Washington coach Norv Turner said Aikman will be a tough
challenge for his secondary. Just last year he threw for 362 and
244 yards in two games against the Redskins. He had seven
touchdowns, five in the season-opener in Washington.
</P>
<P>
   ``From my first-hand experience, I believe Troy's still one of
the better quarterbacks in the league,'' said Turner, who was
Aikman's mentor when he was a Dallas assistant from 1991 to 1993.
</P>
<P>
   NOTEWORTHY
</P>
<P>
   Turner said cornerback Champ Bailey, a two-way player at
Georgia, might play offense Monday. The Redskins are looking for
help in the wake of receiver Michael Westbrook's season-ending
injury....
</P>
<P>
   Last week the Redskins limited Detroit to five field goals, the
first time Washington has held an opponent without a touchdown on
the road in eight years....
</P>
<P>
   Dallas has won five straight games against Washington, the
longest streak for the Cowboys over the Redskins since Dallas won
six straight between 1979 and 1982. The longest winning streak for
the Redskins in the series is four, from 1986 to 1988. Dallas leads
the series 45-33-2....
</P>
<P>
   Washington has explosive players on offense, but the longest
completed pass in two games is only 26 yards....
</P>
<P>
   Rookie cornerback Mario Edwards of Florida State, who has not
played in about a month, returned to practice this week and could
work himself into nickel-package defenses.... Washington rookie
linebacker LaVar Arrington of Penn State might get his first NFL
start on Monday....
</P>
<P>
   The Cowboys have been burned by big plays on defense. They have
yielded three pass-interference penalties for 44, 37 and 26 yards.
The have allowed pass plays of 63 and 26 yards....
</P>
<P>
   Washington receiver Irving Fryar needs one catch to move ahead
of Henry Ellard into sixth on the all-time NFL reception list with
815. He needs only six catches to pass Steve Largent into fifth
place....
</P>
<P>
   The Redskins have allowed one defensive touchdown this season.
It was in the opener against Carolina....
</P>
<P>
   Story Filed By Cox Newspapers
</P>
<P>
   For Use By Clients of the New York Times News Service
</P>
