u f BC-LADN-BUDGET &LR;      09-13 0203
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-LADN-BUDGET </SLUG>
  
<TEXT>
<P>
   The Los Angeles Daily News plans to move the following general
story for use by NYTimes News Service clients, AMs and PMs of
Thursday, Sept. 14, and thereafter. For questions, contact Gerry
Hoppe at the Daily News, (818) 713-3702.
</P>
<P>
   TIMES-LAYOFFS (Los Angeles) _ Acknowledging it failed to attract
readers and advertisers, the Los Angeles Times on Wednesday
abandoned an attempt at intense local news coverage, scuttling 14
``Our Times'' sections and laying off 125 editoral staffers. It is
a wide-ranging retreat and the latest of several changes at the
Times since the paper was acquired by Tribune Co., parent of the
Chicago Tribune. By Greg Wilcox. (Will also move on the ``a''
national and ``n'' California news wires.
</P>
<P>
   STRIKE-ACTORS (Los Angeles) _ Tom Hanks, Alfree Woodard and
nearly 1,000 other actors rallied near the La Brea Tarpits on
Wednesday as their representatives resume negotiations with the
advertising industry in New York. The strike is now in its 19th
week and both sides are hoping for a breakthrough. The strike is
costing Los Angeles County an estimated $1 million in lost business
each work day. By Jesse Hiestand.
</P>
