<P>
   EUROPE-FUEL (London) _ Facing the most serious challenge to his
leadership, Prime Minister Tony Blair calls on protesters to lift
their virtual siege of oil refineries and storage depots, saying
their actions are paralyzing the country and endangering lives.
After a second day of emergency meetings aimed at easing blockades
that have left 90 percent of the country's filling stations dry,
Blair grimly told a news conference that despite the hope he
expressed Tuesday of progress in 24 hours, the situation has only
worsened. By Warren Hoge. (Early version has moved in ``i'' news
file; will be updated by 9 p.m. ET.) 1,400 words.
</P>
