<P>
   VIOLENCE-KIDS (Washington) _ Finally in this election year, the
politicians found something they can agree on: the entertainment
industry should be taken to task for marketing violent movies,
music and video games to children. Sen. Joseph Lieberman told the
Senate Commerce Committee on Wednesday, ``This practice is
outrageous, it is deceptive and it has to stop.'' An hour or so
later, Lynne Cheney said it is even worse than the marketing
practices. By David E. Rosenbaum. (The story has moved in ``w''
news file.) 1,000 words.
</P>
<P>
   With photo, NYT20.
</P>
<P>
   REPUBS-CONGRESS (Washington) _ The Republicans' decision on
Capitol Hill to shift their message to debt reduction and away from
tax cuts in the waning weeks of the session is the latest example
that they are pursuing a campaign strategy independent of Gov.
George W. Bush. While refusing to criticize Bush's large tax plan,
Republican candidates and incumbents on the campaign trail instead
are sticking to a strategy they say has served House Republicans
well this year, emphasizing smaller bite-size tax cuts that target
married couples, small business owners and farmers. By Lizette
Alvarez. (Scheduled to move by 9 p.m. ET in ``p'' news file.)
</P>
