r e BC-NIGHT-FEATURE-LADN &LR;      09-13 0366
</HEADER>
<BODY>
<SLUG> BC-NIGHT-FEATURE-LADN </SLUG>
<HEADLINE>


</HEADLINE>
  
(For use by NYTimes News Service clients) By BOB STRAUSS 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   cc,78p3 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   If you had to follow-up the biggest surprise hit in recent
memory, you'd feel &QL;
</P>
<P>
   a little intimidated, right?
</P>
<P>
   But that's why you're not M. Night Shyamalan and he is. The
Philadelphia-based writer-director confesses to some stress over
the post-production schedule for ``Unbreakable,'' but nly because
the film's Thanksgiving release is coming up fast. Potential
comparisons to his previous supernatural thriller, ``The Sixth
Sense,'' do not trouble him at all.
</P>
<P>
   ``I think it's a cool opportunity to have a really big audience
be excited about what I'm doing next,'' he says. ``That's just a
really nice thing. But the same challenges that were there on
`Sixth Sense' are here again: hoping that we can tell an exciting,
meaningful story in a new way.''
</P>
<P>
   The new film stars ``Sense's'' Bruce Willis as the unscathed
only survivor of a terrible train wreck and Samuel L. Jackson as
the mysterious, brittle-boned stranger who has an unusual theory
about why Willis was spared.
</P>
<P>
   Although the film contains its eerie elements and, Shyamalan
promises, a twist or two a la his previous blockbuster,
``Unbreakable'' is a different movie thematically _ just as its
maker is a different artist than he was 13 months ago.
</P>
<P>
   ``I have a tough time getting up in the morning and coming to
work just because it's a fun or exciting movie,'' Shyamalan admits.
``It really has to have some meaning for me _ and hopefully for an
audience. The characters need to learn lessons that have resonance.
You know, `The Sixth Sense' was as much about parenting and
balancing your work and your marriage as about the kid who saw
ghosts. At the time I wrote it, I'd just become a new parent and
having a career I needed to balance.
</P>
<P>
   ``As for `Unbreakable,' I'm now wondering what I'm going to be
10 years from now, what is my potential versus my tendency to
laziness or whatever; or if I take the wrong path, which way would
it go. These movies tend to reflect what I'm going through at the
time in my life.''
</P>
<P>
   What a life. (Nov. 22) &QL; 
_ Bob Strauss &QL;
</P>
</TEXT>
</BODY>
