<HEADLINE>
`SEX' AND THE SINGLE INTERN
</HEADLINE>
  (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
 
 
By ROB LOWMAN 
c.2000 Los Angeles Daily News 
<TEXT>
<P>
   cc,78p3 &QL;
</P>
<P>
   HBO has announced it bought the rights to Jeffrey Toobin's book
``A Vast &QL;
</P>
<P>
   Conspiracy: The Real Story of the Sex Scandal That Nearly
Brought Down a President,'' a behind-the-scenes look at President
Clinton's impeachment proceedings. So this being cable, we wonder
if we'll get more explicit details than the networks would give us?
</P>
<P>
   And while HBO didn't comment on casting, it won't stop us from
speculating. With Monica Lewinsky's wild weight loss/gain swing, is
HBO looking for an actress to do the Robert De Niro-``Raging Bull''
thing? How many starlets in Tinseltown can do that? (Hint: Monica
has experience.)
</P>
<P>
   And what about playing the Prez? John Travolta, who did good
pseudo- Bill in ``Primary Colors,'' might be available (especially
after ``Battlefield Earth''). But you know there's this Arkansas
politician with the right looks who will be unemployed in
mid-January, and we hear he is looking for a break in Hollywood.
</P>
</TEXT>
