<P>
   BUSH (Monroe, Wash.) _ Visiting a region he described as a
``battleground of environmental war and environmental policy,'' GOP
presidential nominee George W. Bush Wednesday used a cattle farm as
backdrop to extol the joys of nature, praise salmon restoration
projects and pledge a $4.9 billion program to improve upkeep of
national parks.
</P>
<P>
   By Joel Connelly. (Story has moved in the ``a'' category.)
</P>
<P>
   AUTHORS-ATWOOD (Seattle) _ There are books that are as comfy as
an old pair of jeans. Then there are books that raise demands on
readers, like schoolteachers, books that insist that serious
attention be paid, or else. The latest novel by Margaret Atwood is
such a book. ``A story within a story within a story is excessive,
but I'm not writing for people with short attention spans,'' Atwood
says in an interview.
</P>
<P>
   By John Marshall. (Story has moved in the ``e'' category.)
