<HEADLINE>
COWBOYS' WORTHAM EAGER TO MAKE DEBUT AGAINST REDSKINS
</HEADLINE>
 (For use by NYTimes News Service clients) 
By CLARENCE E. HILL JR. 
c.2000 Fort Worth Star-Telegram 
 
 
 
 
<TEXT>
<P>
   IRVING, Texas _ Is it possible for the Cowboys' defense to be
better without middle linebacker Dat Nguyen?
</P>
<P>
   At least for one game, according to the Cowboys.
</P>
<P>
   With Nguyen sidelined two to four weeks because of a sprained
medial collateral ligament in his left knee, former Everman star
Barron Wortham moves into the starting lineup against the
Washington Redskins on Monday night.
</P>
<P>
   Cowboys coach Dave Campo said everything the Redskins do on
offense is predicated off of their power running game. Tailback
Stephen Davis is fourth in the NFL in rushing with 192 yards.
</P>
<P>
   Considering the Cowboys' woeful run defense, stopping the run is
paramount if the Cowboys (0-2) have any hope of ending their losing
ways. Dallas ranks 31st in the league against the run. It has never
finished a season lower than 24th. That dubious distinction came in
1997 when the Cowboys finished 6-10.
</P>
<P>
   ``Stopping the run is our No. 1 priority,'' Campo said. ``We
have to get better against the run.''
</P>
<P>
   Nguyen win situation.]
</P>
<P>
   Nguyen, who won the starting job in training camp, is considered
an undersized linebacker who relies on instinct. However, Wortham,
5-foot-11 and 245 pounds, is an old-fashioned hole plugger.
</P>
<P>
   ``Obviously we made the decision that Dat was the starter. But
\RBarron being in there\S could really help us. Dat may be a little
more squirmier, but Barron is more physical. He is stronger in the
middle than Dat. I think he will play well.''
</P>
<P>
   Without taking anything away from Nguyen, Wortham, a seven-year
veteran, agrees that his style best fits the Cowboys' needs against
the Redskins.
</P>
<P>
   ``I'm one of those old-school type of guys,'' Wortham said.
``The power part of my game is my strength, the physical part.
That's what I like. I really think that's what's going to help us
out on the defensive side of the ball. Not that Dat did a bad job.
Dat is a tremendous linebacker, but I think my game is different
from his.''
</P>
<P>
   Wortham, who signed with the Cowboys during the off-season after
starting on Tennessee's 1999 Super Bowl team, was unable to
showcase his differences when Nguyen won the starting job in
training camp. Wortham injured a knee two weeks into camp and was
sidelined until the final preseason game.
</P>
<P>
   Wortham, however, knows that he would have been hard-pressed to
unseat Nguyen. Nguyen won the starting job because of his long-term
potential, his speed and his ability to cover the pass.
</P>
<P>
   Indeed, Wortham will be replaced in the Cowboys nickel defense
on Sunday by teammate Joe Bowden because of his deficiencies
against the pass.
</P>
<P>
   And Wortham also knows that he will go back to the bench when
Nguyen regains his health. Wortham said he is just trying do his
part in helping the Cowboys win games.
</P>
<P>
   ``I know my role,'' Wortham said. ``Even if it was close in
training camp, they would have started Dat. I'm cool with that. I'm
here in case Dat goes down. That's what they got me here for _
quality depth. Dat went down and I'm here.''
</P>
<P>
   Wortham is not happy about Nguyen's injury, but he is excited to
get more playing time. He has recorded five tackles in two games of
spot duty in place of Nguyen.
</P>
<P>
   ``It's unfortunate that he got hurt, but I like that I get an
opportunity to play,'' Wortham said. ``I haven't really played a
full game since the Super Bowl. When you've been a starter and now
you are behind somebody, you feel like you are missing something
because you are used to being out there. I'm going to have fun with
this.''
</P>
<P>
   Adding to Wortham's excitement is the fact that his first start
for his home-town team is against the rival Redskins on Monday
Night Football. He said he is played this game many times in his
head as a child. He calls it a dream come true.
</P>
<P>
   ``Oh man, that's just a blessing in itself,'' Wortham said.
``Deion \RSanders\S talked about he was born on Monday night.
Monday night might be my night. That's the way I'm looking at it.
I've watched this matchup over the years. John Riggins. Doomsday.
I'm going to take it for what it's worth, relax and have fun.'' nn
</P>
</TEXT>
