<P>
   (NYT17) NEW YORK -- Sept. 13, 2000 -- CHASE-MORGAN-EXEC -- He
may be no Sandy Weill, but William B. Harrison Jr., a 33-year
veteran of Chase, will be overseeing the acquisition of J.P.
Morgan, the boldest merger on Wall Street since the
Citicorp-Travelers deal. Harrison is not a charismatic leader but
is well-regarded for his command of operations and his ability to
dampen volatile egos. Harrison will be president and CEO of J.P.
Morgan Chase. (Chester Higgins Jr./The New York Times) LITE
