Lazio went on the attack against the first lady in their first
debate Wednesday, wielding soundbite-sized insults and an actual
prop in his hand. NBC spokeswoman Barb Levin said Lazio violated an
agreement both campaigns had made not to use props when he produced
a contract that would ban the use of unregulated donations. Lazio
and Clinton during their first of three debates. (James Estrin/The
New York Times)
