emerged. Mary Peng, who sells $50 Chinese wedding baskets and
$3,500 Chinese antiques out of her Manhattan loft, says ``The
younger collectors are seasoned travelers in their 20's, coming
back to the United States, who want to purchase the furniture they
had seen overseas, and who know that antiques don't have to be
$10,000 to start.'' (Fred R. Conrad/The New York Times)
