<P>
   (NYT10) PASADENA, Calif -- Sept. 13, 2000 -- CIR-QUAKE-SITE --
The U.S. Geological Survey Earthquake has set up a site that people
can log into after a quake and according to their responses builds
a map of quake effects. Dr. David Wald, a seismologist, in his
office at the U.S. Geological Survey showing the results of
responses to the 1994 Northridge, Cali., earthquake. Wald created
the Web site to monitor the intensity of earthquakes.(Marissa
Roth/The New York Times)
