<P>
   (NYT7) NEW YORK -- Sept. 13, 2000 -- NY-AS-EMPIRE-2 -- ``Art and
the Empire City: New York, 1825-1861,'' a major new exhibition at
the Metropolitan Museum of Art that opens next Tuesday, highlights
the era when New York grew exponentially from a promising
provincial port city to the largest metropolis in the Western
Hemisphere, the locus of American trade, culture and the arts.
Pascale Patris, assistant conservator in the Metropolitan Museum of
Art's Department of Objects Conservation, works on the frame of
Samuel Morris' portrait of the Marquis de Lafayette in preparation
for the exhibit. (Ruth Fremson/The New York Times)
</P>
<P>
   (NYT6) NEW YORK -- Sept. 13, 2000 -- NY-AS-EMPIRE -- ``Art and
the Empire City: New York, 1825-1861,'' a major new exhibition at
